I cannot generate binary PNG image files as text output. Screenshot test snapshot images are binary files that must be generated by actually running the visual regression tests and capturing the rendered output.

To properly update this snapshot, you need to:

1. Run the screenshot tests with the `--updateSnapshot` flag (e.g., `npm test -- --updateSnapshot` or `yarn test --updateSnapshot`)
2. The test framework will automatically generate the new baseline snapshot images based on the current rendered output
3. Commit the updated/new snapshot images to the repository

The snapshot file `radio-button-screenshot-test-tsx-radio-button-negative-mobile-ios-1-snap.png` needs to be generated by the test runner, not manually created.
